records.addlTxt:
3:33 PM Defendant Everett J Hembrook in court, in custody.  Attorney J Andrew Herbers Jr. in court for Everett J Hembrook.  Prosecuting attorney Kristi J Gordon in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case called for plea and sentencing.
Court conducts plea colloquy.  Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty.  Counts 2 and 3 are dismissed and read in.
Recommendations by the State.  Recommendations by the Defense.  Statement by defendant.


The Court Orders the Following:

Count 1:
6 Years Imprisonment (Credit - 118 Days)
-	3 Years of Initial Confinement
-	3 Years of Extended Supervision

Defendant is not eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program
Defendant is not eligible for the Substance Abuse Program

Conditions of Extended Supervision:
-	Mental Health evaluation and follow through with any treatment recommended;
-	Absolute Sobriety; 
-	Random U.A.'s;
-	No Use or Possession of alcohol or illegal drugs or drug paraphernalia;
-	All prescriptions to be filled at the same pharmacy
-	Inform agent of all prescriptions;
-	Complete Thinking for a Change Course;
-	Maintain full time employment (35 hours per week);
-	Obtain a valid Driver's License within the first 12 months of extended supervision and maintain it;
-	No new law violations;

COSTS:  $ 268.00

DNA Surcharge: $ 250.00

DNA Sample ordered and to be provided immediately if in custody or within (3) business days at the Waukesha County Sheriff Department. 

Total costs/fine/forfeiture:  to be paid as a condition of extended supervision. Failure to pay;  will result in a civil judgment.

Felony warnings, immigration warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
